    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation level for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at Gradation 1 per MRL 2 scoping. The validation results demonstrate NIH prediction error of 11.3%, within the 15% acceptance band. The steady-state comparator mismatch with the pulsatile COU was noted but accepted on the basis of the team's conservative-bound assertion. The missing comparedAgainst link in the primary validation result was treated as an administrative omission rather than a substantive gap. On balance, the credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the decision to use CFD hemolysis predictions for identifying worst-case operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
